Later, he pushed to the line of fire and led the line forward with the "greatest bravery" before firing a field gun in the single line and eliminating three of the military units.
Colonel Vann was shot by a German sniper on October 4, 1918; a little more than a month before the end of the war.
Michael Vann, 72, said that his grandfather's actions were something he could never do, and at the same time something that makes one humble.
Together with his brother Dr. James Vann, he laid a wreath after the parade under the direction of the Brentwood Imperial Youth Band.
